{"id":"afflictions","term":"Afflictions","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Common to all (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 5:7\">Job 5:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 14:1\">14:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 34:19\">Ps. 34:19</a>); are for the good of men (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 1:2\">James 1:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 1:3\">3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 1:12\">12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Corinthians 12:7\">2 Cor. 12:7</a>) and the glory of God (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Corinthians 12:7\">2 Cor. 12:7-10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 4:14\">1 Pet. 4:14</a>), and are to be borne with patience by the Lord’s people (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 94:12\">Ps. 94:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 3:12\">Prov. 3:12</a>). They are all directed by God (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Lamentations 3:33\">Lam. 3:33</a>), and will result in the everlasting good of his people (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Corinthians 4:16\">2 Cor. 4:16-18</a>) in Christ Jesus (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 8:35\">Rom. 8:35-39</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Job 5:7","Job 14:1","Psalms 34:19","James 1:2","James 1:3","James 1:12","2 Corinthians 12:7","1 Peter 4:14","Psalms 94:12","Proverbs 3:12","Lamentations 3:33","2 Corinthians 4:16","Romans 8:35"]}